  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you choose an unresponsive yoyo?",
  "response": "Choosing an unresponsive yoyo involves understanding its characteristics and ensuring it meets your skill level and preferences. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you pick the right one:\n\n### 1. **Understand What \"Unresponsive\" Means**\nAn unresponsive yoyo does not return to your hand with a simple tug. Instead, it requires a specific technique (like a \"bind\") to return. This makes it ideal for advanced tricks and string manipulation.\n\n### 2. **Determine Your Skill Level**\n- **Beginner**: If you\u2019re new to yoyoing, it\u2019s better to start with a responsive yoyo to learn the basics. Transition to unresponsive once you\u2019re comfortable with foundational tricks.\n- **Intermediate/Advanced**: If you\u2019ve mastered basic tricks and want to tackle more complex maneuvers, an unresponsive yoyo is the way to go.\n\n### 3. **Choose the Right Shape and Size**\nFor unresponsive yoyos:\n- **Shape**: Look for **organic**, **H-shaped**, or **V-shaped** designs. These shapes balance stability and playability for advanced tricks.\n- **Size**: Standard sizes (50-56mm) are versatile and suitable for most players. Larger yoyos are more stable, while smaller ones are faster.\n\n### 4. **Consider Weight and Material**\n- **Weight**: 60-70 grams is ideal for unresponsive yoyos. Lighter yoyos are faster, while heavier ones are more stable.\n- **Material**: Aluminum is the most common and durable material for unresponsive yoyos. It provides a smooth and consistent performance.\n\n### 5. **Check the Bearing**\nUnresponsive yoyos use a **wide bearing** (size C) that allows for longer spins and doesn\u2019t respond to light tugs. Ensure the bearing is clean and smooth for optimal performance.\n\n### 6. **Look for Adjustable Features**\nSome yoyos come with adjustable response systems (e.g., silicone pads or starburst response). This allows you to customize the yoyo\u2019s play style.\n\n### 7. **Set a Budget**\nUnresponsive yoyos range from $20 to $100+. High-end yoyos offer better performance and durability, but there are excellent budget options for beginners.\n\n### 8. **Research Brands and Reviews**\nPopular brands like **YoYoFactory**, **MagicYoYo**, and **CLYW** are known for quality unresponsive yoyos. Read reviews and watch videos to see how the yoyo performs.\n\n### 9. **Try Before You Buy**\nIf possible, test the yoyo at a store or borrow one from a friend. This will help you get a feel for its weight, balance, and spin time.\n\n### 10. **Popular Unresponsive Yoyo Recommendations**\n- **YoYoFactory Shutter**: Great for beginners and advanced players alike.\n- **MagicYoYo N12 Shark Honor**: Affordable and high-performing.\n- **CLYW Arctic Circle 2**: Smooth and stylish for experienced players.\n\nBy considering these factors, you\u2019ll be able to choose an unresponsive yoyo that suits your needs and enhances your yoyoing experience!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
